cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper presents a generative model for super-resolution in MRI images, which involves using a prior based on multi-channel total variation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category, as it deals with image processing and analysis. Additionally, the paper mentions handling bias-variance trade-off through hyper-parameter estimation, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also validates the model on a large database of brain images, indicating that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of a forward model to simulate the slice-select profile of the MR scanner suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
